You are a security researcher analyzing an HR portal's persistent-login token used to keep employees signed in to a records system.

The portal is a traditional Java EE web application that serves employee records. To avoid asking staff to re-authenticate every morning, a "stay signed in" token is minted at login and validated on return visits. The token is produced and consumed by Apache Shiro 1.4.1's AesCipherService, and its value is base64(IV || ciphertext) carried in a cookie. A small service class centralizes the mint-and-verify logic so controllers never touch the cipher directly.

