Verification delegates to Shiro's CookieRememberMeManager, which calls AesCipherService.decrypt on the cookie. The routine base64-decodes the value, peels the leading 16-byte IV, and decrypts the rest under AES in CBC mode, stripping PKCS5 padding at the end. An invalid pad makes the underlying cipher throw, and Shiro maps that to "cookie rejected", which is observably distinct from a token that decrypts to a valid employee identifier. Since the design adds no MAC or authenticated mode, that binary outcome leaks padding correctness for every cookie an attacker submits.

