Students who choose to stay logged in receive a cookie that the LMS later decrypts to resume their session. The platform wires Apache Shiro 1.4.1's AesCipherService into the Spring context as a bean, and a component assembles the cookie value as base64(IV || ciphertext). The cipher key is injected once at construction, and a small builder configures the service before any request is served.

